[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is there a notational way to distinguish horizontal and vertical composition? I feel like I've seen <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span></span></span></span> for both.</p>",
        "id": 215190167,
        "sender_full_name": "Shea Levy",
        "timestamp": 1604148480
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Some people use <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.59445em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span> denotes the dimensionality of composition</p>",
        "id": 215190374,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1604148749
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>For a k-cell, you have <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mn>1</mn></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mo>∘</mo><mi>k</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_1, \\dots, \\circ_k</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.63889em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">…</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.33610799999999996em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, where <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mn>1</mn></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.59445em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> denotes composition along the <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span></span></span></span>-boundary, and so on.</p>",
        "id": 215190399,
        "sender_full_name": "Fabrizio Genovese",
        "timestamp": 1604148803
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Should be <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mn>0</mn></msub><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mo>…</mo><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><msub><mo>∘</mo><mrow><mi>k</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_0, \\ldots, \\circ_{k-1}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6527810000000001em;vertical-align:-0.208331em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.30110799999999993em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">0</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"minner\">…</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.16666666666666666em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.3361079999999999em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\" style=\"margin-right:0.03148em;\">k</span><span class=\"mbin mtight\">−</span><span class=\"mord mtight\">1</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.208331em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, but yes.</p>",
        "id": 215191803,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1604150885
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If it's just 2-categories you could also use <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>⊗</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\otimes</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.66666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">⊗</span></span></span></span> for horizontal, as in monoidal categories. I think that's what Cockett and Seely use, possibly others too.</p>",
        "id": 215191881,
        "sender_full_name": "Amar Hadzihasanovic",
        "timestamp": 1604151014
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"351475\">Shea Levy</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/229199-learning.3A-questions/topic/Notation.20for.202-cell.20compositions.3F/near/215190167\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Is there a notational way to distinguish horizontal and vertical composition? I feel like I've seen <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span></span></span></span> for both.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>\\boxvert, and \\boxminus, of course! (I never remember which one is already defined, the one that isn't is just a \\mathop of the \\rotatebox{90} of the other.</p>",
        "id": 215197981,
        "sender_full_name": "fosco",
        "timestamp": 1604160363
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Personally, I find it most intuitive to use <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span></span></span></span> for horizontal composition, because it's in the same direction as 1-categorical composition, and then one can use some other symbol, e.g. <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∙</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\bullet</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∙</span></span></span></span>, for vertical composition.</p>",
        "id": 215239970,
        "sender_full_name": "Nathanael Arkor",
        "timestamp": 1604230079
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This convention would mean that if <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>α</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>F</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>G</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\alpha : F \\to G</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.43056em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>β</mi><mo>:</mo><mi>G</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>H</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\beta : G \\to H</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8888799999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">:</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">G</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.08125em;\">H</span></span></span></span> are natural transformations, the notation for their composition would depend on whether you're currently viewing them as 2-morphisms of Cat or 1-morphisms of a category of functors... which seems like a pretty thin distinction to draw.</p>",
        "id": 215240723,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604231250
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>In practice I think most people would just denote both kinds of composition by juxtaposition and let context disambiguate.</p>",
        "id": 215240727,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604231263
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I've always seen people use separate notations, and this seems pretty important, since one often uses both kinds of  composition together,  e.g. in the interchange law</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>β</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>⊗</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi>α</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo>∘</mo><msup><mi>β</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mo>⊗</mo><msup><mi>α</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>∘</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>β</mi><mo>⊗</mo><msup><mi>β</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> (\\alpha \\circ \\beta) \\otimes (\\alpha' \\circ \\beta') = (\\alpha \\otimes \\alpha') \\circ (\\beta \\otimes \\beta') </annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">⊗</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>\n<p>which if one denotes both forms of composition by juxtaposition becomes</p>\n<p><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><mi>β</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msup><mi>α</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><msup><mi>β</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>α</mi><msup><mi>α</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>β</mi><msup><mi>β</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" mathvariant=\"normal\" rspace=\"0em\">′</mo></msup><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\"> (\\alpha \\beta) (\\alpha' \\beta') = (\\alpha \\alpha') (\\beta \\beta') </annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.001892em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.0037em;\">α</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.05278em;\">β</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.751892em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">′</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></p>",
        "id": 215249654,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1604245726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess I've also heard of <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∗</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">*</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.46528em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∗</span></span></span></span> being used for horizontal composition. It doesn't come up too often, anyways.</p>",
        "id": 215260387,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604261899
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>At the point where the notation starts to become nonobvious, it would be better to have a diagram.</p>",
        "id": 215260395,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604261938
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Some days I use horizontal and vertical composition in 2-categories all day long.    I've used various notations at various times, since I don't think there's a standard one.  The main thing is to explain your notation.</p>",
        "id": 215261640,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1604263650
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm thinking of situations in ordinary category theory, like the triangular equations for an adjunction.</p>",
        "id": 215262979,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604265887
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd expect to see something like <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mi>ε</mi><mi>F</mi><mo>∘</mo><mi>F</mi><mi>η</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">1 = \\varepsilon F \\circ F \\eta</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.64444em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">1</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">ε</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8777699999999999em;vertical-align:-0.19444em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.03588em;\">η</span></span></span></span>, with an explicit <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo>∘</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.44445em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\">∘</span></span></span></span> for clarity, but otherwise using juxtaposition where possible. I'd be surprised to see <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.59445em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> or any notation which needed explanation.</p>",
        "id": 215263056,
        "sender_full_name": "Reid Barton",
        "timestamp": 1604266017
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mo>∘</mo><mi>i</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\circ_i</annotation></semantics></math></span><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"katex-html\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.59445em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mbin\">∘</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.31166399999999994em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">i</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> tends to show up when you hit 3-categories or higher.</p>",
        "id": 215263748,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1604267053
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I use a lot of mixtures of horizontal and vertical composition of natural transformations in category theory, but as you suggest, it's best to describe these using 2-categorical pasting diagrams: they're a lot clearer.</p>",
        "id": 215263786,
        "sender_full_name": "John Baez",
        "timestamp": 1604267139
    }
]